The article announces the appointments and nominations of three individuals to key positions within the U.S. government. Shailen P. Bhatt, from Michigan, has been chosen as the Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration, replacing Nicole R. Nason. Jeffrey Matthew Marootian, from the District of Columbia, has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Energy, specifically in charge of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy, taking the place of Daniel Simmons. Lastly, Stephen A. Owens, from Arizona, has been nominated to serve as the Chairperson of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board for a five-year term, replacing Katherine Andrea Lemos who is resigning.